thread.title: Don’t Count on This Earnings Bonanza Lasting - MoneyBeat - WSJ

author: Ben Eisen
title: Don’t Count on This Earnings Bonanza Lasting - MoneyBeat - WSJ
text: Companies are wrapping up a stellar earnings season, but the rest of the year might not be as hot. With 91% of S&P 500 companies reporting results for the first three months of 2018, earnings are expected to have grown 25% versus the prior year, according to FactSet. That would be the best quarter since OPEC’s Oil Production Crept Up Last Month—Energy Journal Next Stocks to Watch: Tesla, Alphabet, Xerox, Sears, Qualcomm, NXP, Walmart, JPMorgan, Ford, HP
